  "plot_summary": "While not really an announcement, both the <i>Hulk</i> and <i>Fantastic Four</i> magazines cross-promoted each other in the full-page <i>Now on Sale</i> ads, with the FF being called the Hulk's \"companion magazine.\"",
  "meanwhile": {
    "before": "During the early months of 1962, Marvel still hadn't reached the point where they released more than about one book per month that was actually part of the early Marvel Universe, so rather than do monthly summaries with so few, I decided to lump these early months of the year into one group to be considered together.\n\nWith that being said, here are all the other books published by Marvel between the months of January-May, 1962:",
