  "review_text": "There were only four graded books over this five-month period, which due to the dreadful showing of <i>Incredible Hulk</i> #2, dragged the average down to a mere [SPAN: severity=info; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=5.83].&nbsp; It would have been much closer to full upper-mid-grade had Stan and Jack simply decided to not publish that issue at all, but what's done is done.\n\nLike a newborn calf, the company totters a bit getting to its feet for the first time, so it's really not that surprising that there will be some stumbling ahead...\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** SUMMARY_BEGIN ***\n*** THIS MONTH ***4 graded stories over 4 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 4 grade character issue   weight 8.0   ff        FF #5   1 7.5   ff        FF #4   1 5.0   hulk      HULK #1 1 1.0   hulk      HULK #2 15.38*** LAST MONTH ***1 graded stories over 1 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 1 grade character issue weight 8.0   ff        FF #5 18.00\n*** SUMMARY_END ***]",
  "letters_page": "[HANG0] * Without question, the introduction of Dr. Doom tops the list, with the Silver Age <i>re</i>-introduction of the Sub-Mariner being just behind.&nbsp; But of course, the addition of the Hulk (Bruce Banner) is also significant, with Rick Jones, Betty Ross and General \"Thunderbolt\" Ross rounding out the rest of the new arrivals.\n[DEVNOTE: *** INTRODUCTION_BEGIN ***\nNotes | first | villain | death | Giganto\nBetty Ross | Milestone: (first)\nBruce Banner (Hulk) | Milestone: (first), (origin)\nGargoyle | villain | Milestone: (first), (death)\nGeneral Ross | Milestone: (first)\nRick Jones | Milestone: (first)\nNotes | first | villain | Igor Drenkov\nNotes | first | Linda Brown\nNotes | first | \"Aunt May\\\nNotes | first | \"Uncle Ben\\\nDr. Doom | villain | Milestone: (first), (origin: - partial)\nNotes | first | villain | Toad Men\n*** INTRODUCTION_END ***]\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_BEGIN ***]\n[HANG0] * Johnny Storm finds a homeless man, burns off his beard, and accidentally resurrects the Golden Age.\n[HANG0] * Gamma radiation gives Marvel a new hero, even if the comic isn't sure what to do with him yet.\n[HANG0] * Dr. Doom's first appearance instantly elevates the FF's world, introducing a villain whose ambition and mystique dwarf anything the series has attempted so far.\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_END ***]\n[HANG0] * The jury is still out on whether this new \"Hulk\" character is worth a further look....things don't appear promising at this early stage....perhaps he's a bust??",
  "ownership": "Looking ahead, one of the most significant months in the history of Marvel Comics, as on the very same day, we're introduced to an unpopular teenager destined to be caught up in a web of....well <i>something</i>, a lame doctor who stumbles across a walking stick in Norway, and a second look at Henry Pym, who this time decides to stick with his original formula seen a few months ago.&nbsp; And only a week later, we're treated to the first-ever super-villain team-up in Marvel's brief history!"
}